text: Alfta-Ösa OK is an Swedish sport club from Alfta, specialising in orienteering and ski orienteering. It was established in 1980 by merging Alfta SOK and ÖSA OK. Alfta-Ösa OK won the Venla relay in 2017 with a team consisting of Galina Vinogradova, Josefine Heikka, Sara Eskilsson and Natalia Gemperle. == Sources == Category:Orienteering clubs in Sweden Category:Hälsingland
